  `cf2_input_type` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'test_box',
  `cf2_input_options` text,
  `cf3_input_type` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'test_box',
  `cf3_input_options` text,
  `cf4_input_type` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'test_box',
  `cf4_input_options` text,
  `cf5_input_type` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'test_box',
  `cf5_input_options` text,
  `cf6_input_type` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'test_box',
  `cf6_input_options` text,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=6 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

  `is_active` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=10 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_skrill
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_skrill`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_skrill` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `active` tinyint(4) NOT NULL,
  `account_email` varchar(255) NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  `secret_word` varchar(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  `skrill_currency` varchar(3) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'INR',
  `fixed_charges` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0.0000',
  `extra_charges_my` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0.0000',
  `extra_charges_other` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0.0000',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_sms_configs
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_sms_configs`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_sms_configs` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `template_name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `template_key` varchar(100) NOT NULL,
  `dlt_te_id` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Simplysafe Default Id',
  `client_dlt_te_id` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Client Personal Id',
  `sms_format` text NOT NULL,
  `is_active` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1',
  `updated_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_by` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_stock_count_items
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_stock_count_items`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_stock_count_items` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `stock_count_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_code` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_name` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_variant` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_variant_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `expected` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `counted` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `cost` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `stock_count_id` (`stock_count_id`),
  KEY `product_id` (`product_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_stock_counts
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_stock_counts`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_stock_counts` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `date` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `reference_no` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `type` varchar(10) NOT NULL,
  `initial_file` varchar(50) NOT NULL,
  `final_file` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `brands` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `brand_names` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `categories` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `category_names` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `note` text,
  `products` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `rows` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `differences` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `matches` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `missing` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_by` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `updated_by` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  `finalized` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `warehouse_id` (`warehouse_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=2 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

INSERT INTO `sma_stock_counts` (`id`, `date`, `reference_no`, `warehouse_id`, `type`, `initial_file`, `final_file`, `brands`, `brand_names`, `categories`, `category_names`, `note`, `products`, `rows`, `differences`, `matches`, `missing`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `updated_at`, `finalized`) VALUES ('1', '2022-02-04 14:06:00', '', '1', 'full', '2bde15d193736f6ed07ba0e4ee28e0b5.csv', NULL, '', '', '', '', NULL, '23', '23', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL);

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_suspended_items
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_suspended_items`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_suspended_items` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `suspend_id` int(11) unsigned NOT NULL,
  `product_id` int(11) unsigned NOT NULL,
  `product_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `article_code` varchar(60) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `net_unit_price` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL,
  `unit_price` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL,
  `quantity` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT '0.0000',
  `warehouse_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `item_tax` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `tax_rate_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `tax` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `discount` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `item_discount` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `subtotal` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL,
  `serial_no` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `option_id` int(11) DEFAULT '0',
  `batch_number` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_type` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL,
  `real_unit_price` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_unit_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_unit_code` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `unit_quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `mrp` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL,
  `net_price` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL COMMENT 'MRP x Qty.',
  `hsn_code` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `isdelivered` tinyint(4) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  `note` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `invoice_net_unit_price` decimal(19,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `invoice_total_net_unit_price` decimal(19,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `invoice_unit_price` decimal(19,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `tax_method` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT '0:Inclusive, 1:Exclusive',
  `unit_discount` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `unit_tax` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `item_weight` decimal(8,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=15 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_themes

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_themes`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_themes` (
  `id` int(1) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `theme_name` varchar(62) NOT NULL,
  `theme_label` varchar(62) DEFAULT NULL,
  `is_active` int(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1',
  `is_delete` int(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=3 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_transfer_items
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_transfer_items`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_transfer_items` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `transfer_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `product_name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `option_id` int(11) DEFAULT '0',
  `batch_number` varchar(60) DEFAULT NULL,
  `expiry` date DEFAULT NULL,
  `quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `request_quantity` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `sent_quantity` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `tax_rate_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `tax` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `item_tax` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `net_unit_cost` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `subtotal` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `quantity_balance` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `unit_cost` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `real_unit_cost` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `date` date DEFAULT NULL,
  `warehouse_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_unit_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_unit_code` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `unit_quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `item_status` varchar(30) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Item Transfer Status',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `transfer_id` (`transfer_id`),
  KEY `product_id` (`product_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_transfer_request
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_transfer_request`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_transfer_request` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `transfer_request_no` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `date` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `from_warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `from_warehouse_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `from_warehouse_name` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `from_warehouse_state_code` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_name` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_state_code` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `note` varchar(1000) DEFAULT NULL,
  `total` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `total_tax` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `grand_total` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_by` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `status` varchar(55) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',
  `shipping` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0.0000',
  `attachment` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_at` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `id` (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_transfer_request_items
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_transfer_request_items`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_transfer_request_items` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `transfer_request_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `product_name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `option_id` int(11) DEFAULT '0',
  `batch_number` varchar(60) DEFAULT NULL,
  `expiry` date DEFAULT NULL,
  `quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `request_quantity` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `sent_quantity` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `quantity_balance` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `tax_rate_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `tax` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `item_tax` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `net_unit_cost` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `subtotal` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `unit_cost` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `real_unit_cost` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `date` date DEFAULT NULL,
  `warehouse_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_unit_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_unit_code` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `unit_quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `item_status` varchar(30) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Item Transfer Status',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `transfer_id` (`transfer_request_id`),
  KEY `product_id` (`product_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_transfers
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_transfers`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_transfers` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `transfer_no` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `date` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `from_warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `from_warehouse_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `from_warehouse_name` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_code` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_name` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `note` varchar(1000) DEFAULT NULL,
  `total` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `total_tax` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `grand_total` decimal(25,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_by` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `status` varchar(55) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',
  `shipping` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0.0000',
  `attachment` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_at` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `from_warehouse_state_code` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `to_warehouse_state_code` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `transfer_request_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `transfer_request_no` varchar(30) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `id` (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=4 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_logs
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_logs`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_logs` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `order_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `channel` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT ' zomato, foodpanda, swiggy, ubereats',
  `response_json` text,
  `log_type` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `order_status` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_at` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_orderrider
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_orderrider`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_orderrider` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `up_order_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Urbanpiper order id',
  `channel_name` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'urbanpiper, zomato, foodpanda, swiggy,  ubereats',
  `channel_order_id` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'channel order id',
  `current_state` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'At store, assigned',
  `alt_phone` bigint(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'delivery person alt phone no',
  `name` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'delivery person name',
  `phone` bigint(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'delivery person  phone no',
  `comments` text,
  `order_status` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'assigned, at-store, unassigned, re-assigned, out-for-delivery, delivered',
  `created` timestamp NULL DEFAULT NULL,
  `up_order_rider_response` longtext COMMENT 'Urbanpiper response order rider',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_package_logs
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_package_logs`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_package_logs` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `package_orders` int(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `balance_order` int(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_products
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_products`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_products` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `product_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_code` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `price` decimal(15,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `food_type_id` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `active_status` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `add_status` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `plat_urbanpiper` text COMMENT 'UrbanPiper Tags',
  `plat_zomato` text COMMENT 'Zomato Tags',
  `plat_foodpanda` text COMMENT 'Foodpanda tags',
  `plat_swiggy` text COMMENT 'Swiggy Tags',
  `plat_ubereats` text COMMENT 'Ubereats Tags',
  `default_tag` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'default_tag',
  `available` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `sold_at_store` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `recommended` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `manage_stock` tinyint(4) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=2 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

INSERT INTO `sma_up_products` (`id`, `product_id`, `product_code`, `price`, `food_type_id`, `active_status`, `add_status`, `plat_urbanpiper`, `plat_zomato`, `plat_foodpanda`, `plat_swiggy`, `plat_ubereats`, `default_tag`, `available`, `sold_at_store`, `recommended`, `manage_stock`) VALUES ('1', '229', '38002374', '799.0000', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '0', NULL);


#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_products_platform
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_products_platform`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_products_platform` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `up_store_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `up_store_ref_id` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `product_code` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `active_status` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `add_status` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `urbanpiper` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `zomato` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `foodpanda` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `swiggy` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `ubereats` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `available` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `sold_at_store` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `recommended` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `tag_urbanpiper` text,
  `tag_zomato` text,
  `tag_swiggy` text,
  `tag_foodpanda` text,
  `tag_ubereats` text,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_stores
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_stores`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_stores` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `name` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `ref_id` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'id_code',
  `warehouse_id` tinyint(4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `city` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `email` varchar(60) DEFAULT NULL,
  `contact_phone` bigint(20) DEFAULT NULL,
  `notification_phones` text COMMENT 'multiple phone number store using  ","  separate',
  `notification_emails` text COMMENT 'multiple email id store using  ","  separate',
  `address` text,
  `zip_codes` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'multiple zipcode store using  ","  separate',
  `min_pickup_time` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `min_delivery_time` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `min_order_value` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `hide_from_ui` tinyint(4) DEFAULT '0',
  `geo_longitude` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `active` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `geo_latitude` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `ordering_enabled` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `translations` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'hi: Hindi, ar: Arabic, ja: Japanese, pt: Portugues, fr: French, es: Spanish',
  `store_add_urbanpiper` int(11) DEFAULT '0' COMMENT 'Urbanpiper Store Add value = 1 or Not Add  value=0',
  `urbanpiper_reference` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Urbenpiper response reference Id',
  `days` text NOT NULL,
  `store_start_time` time DEFAULT NULL,
  `store_close_time` time DEFAULT NULL,
  `plat_urbanpiper` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'platform : enable, disable',
  `plat_zomato` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'platform : enable, disable',
  `plat_foodpanda` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'platform : enable, disable',
  `plat_swiggy` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'platform : enable, disable',
  `plat_ubereats` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'platform : enable, disable',
  `excluded_platforms` text,
  `included_platforms` text,
  `created_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  UNIQUE KEY `ref_id` (`ref_id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=4 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_up_stores_categories
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_up_stores_categories`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_up_stores_categories` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `category_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `parent_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `parent_ref_id` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `store_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `category_ref_id` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `store_ref_id` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `up_is_active` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `up_added` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_user_action_logs
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_user_action_logs`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_user_action_logs` (
  `id` bigint(11) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `user_id` int(1) NOT NULL,
  `user_name` varchar(60) NOT NULL,
  `action_type` varchar(60) NOT NULL,
  `product_id` int(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `quantity` int(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `action_reff_id` text,
  `action_affected_data` text,
  `action_comment` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `action_url` text NOT NULL,
  `created_at` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updated_at` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `is_active` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1',
  `is_delete` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=149 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_user_logins
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_user_logins`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_user_logins` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `user_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `company_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `ip_address` varbinary(16) NOT NULL,
  `login` varchar(100) NOT NULL,
  `time` timestamp NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=178 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_users
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_users`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_users` (
  `id` int(11) unsigned NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `last_ip_address` varbinary(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `ip_address` varbinary(45) NOT NULL,
  `username` varchar(100) NOT NULL,
  `password` varchar(40) NOT NULL,
  `salt` varchar(40) DEFAULT NULL,
  `email` varchar(100) NOT NULL,
  `activation_code` varchar(40) DEFAULT NULL,
  `forgotten_password_code` varchar(40) DEFAULT NULL,
  `forgotten_password_time` int(11) unsigned DEFAULT NULL,
  `remember_code` varchar(40) DEFAULT NULL,
  `created_on` int(11) unsigned NOT NULL,
  `last_login` int(11) unsigned DEFAULT NULL,
  `active` tinyint(1) unsigned DEFAULT NULL,
  `first_name` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `last_name` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `company` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `phone` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL,
  `avatar` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `gender` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL,
  `group_id` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL,
  `warehouse_id` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `biller_id` int(10) unsigned DEFAULT NULL,
  `company_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `show_cost` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `show_price` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `award_points` int(11) DEFAULT '0',
  `view_right` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `edit_right` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `allow_discount` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `offline_mobile_app_access` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1' COMMENT 'Android App Access',
  `offline_windows_app_access` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1' COMMENT 'Windows Localhost Offline App Access',
  `updated_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `group_id` (`group_id`,`warehouse_id`,`biller_id`),
  KEY `group_id_2` (`group_id`,`company_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=16 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_variants
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_variants`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_variants` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `name` varchar(55) NOT NULL,
  `updated_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_warehouses
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_warehouses`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_warehouses` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `code` varchar(50) NOT NULL,
  `name` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `address` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `city` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `state` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `state_code` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `postal_code` varchar(12) DEFAULT NULL,
  `country` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `map` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `phone` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `email` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `price_group_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `in_eshop` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `is_active` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1',
  `is_deleted` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0',
  `is_disabled` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0' COMMENT 'For Simply POSAdmin',
  `pos_biller_id` int(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `eshop_biller_id` int(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `id` (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=7 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_warehouses_products
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_warehouses_products`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_warehouses_products` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `product_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `rack` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `avg_cost` decimal(25,4) NOT NULL,
  `updated_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `product_id` (`product_id`),
  KEY `warehouse_id` (`warehouse_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=85 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_warehouses_products_variants
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_warehouses_products_variants`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_warehouses_products_variants` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `option_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `product_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `warehouse_id` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `quantity` decimal(15,4) NOT NULL,
  `rack` varchar(55) DEFAULT NULL,
  `updated_at` timestamp NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `option_id` (`option_id`),
  KEY `product_id` (`product_id`),
  KEY `warehouse_id` (`warehouse_id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=4 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_webshop_features
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_webshop_features`;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_webshop_settings
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_webshop_settings`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_webshop_settings` (
  `id` tinyint(1) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `home_page` varchar(200) NOT NULL,
  `product_list_page` varchar(200) DEFAULT 'list_page_filterbar',
  `product_list_view` varchar(200) DEFAULT 'list_grid',
  `product_description` varchar(200) NOT NULL,
  `theme_color` varchar(50) DEFAULT 'blue',
  `header_strip_style` varchar(30) DEFAULT '9' COMMENT '1: Lite / 9: Dark',
  `header_style` varchar(50) DEFAULT 'header_fixed_searchbar' COMMENT 'header_fixed_searchbar / header_fixed_menubar',
  `updated_at` datetime NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `biller_id` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '3',
  `warehouse_id` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `overselling` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `rounding` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1',
  `cod` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '1' COMMENT 'Cash On Delivery',
  `online_payment` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `free_delivery_above_amount` decimal(9,4) DEFAULT NULL,
  `active_offer` tinyint(1) DEFAULT NULL,
  `suport_email` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `suport_phone` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `logo` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `favicon` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `return_within_days` int(1) DEFAULT '10',
  `active_multi_outlets` tinyint(1) DEFAULT '0',
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=2 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_webshop_sliders
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_webshop_sliders`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_webshop_sliders` (
  `id` int(1) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `slide_key` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL,
  `slide_image` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `background_image` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `title` varchar(200) DEFAULT NULL,
  `sub_title` varchar(200) DEFAULT NULL,
  `title_color` varchar(10) DEFAULT '#000000',
  `subtitle_color` varchar(10) DEFAULT '#000000',
  `button_caption` varchar(50) DEFAULT NULL,
  `button_link` varchar(255) DEFAULT NULL,
  `bottom_caption` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `is_active` char(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1',
  `is_updated` char(1) DEFAULT '0',
  `updated_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  UNIQUE KEY `slide_key` (`slide_key`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=3 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

#
# TABLE STRUCTURE FOR: sma_webshop_static_pages
#

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `sma_webshop_static_pages`;

CREATE TABLE `sma_webshop_static_pages` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `page_key` varchar(60) DEFAULT NULL,
  `page_title` varchar(250) DEFAULT NULL,
  `page_file` varchar(250) DEFAULT NULL,
  `page_text` longtext,
  `page_type` varchar(10) DEFAULT NULL,
  `page_section` varchar(20) DEFAULT NULL,
  `is_active` tinyint(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1',
  `updated_at` datetime DEFAULT NULL ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM AUTO_INCREMENT=11 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

Also, we may disclose your Personal Information to the police, regulatory bodies or legal advisers in connection with any alleged criminal offence or suspected breach of this Privacy Policy and or the breach of other terms and conditions otherwise relating to you or otherwise where required by law and we will co-operate with any law enforcement authorities or court order requesting or directing us to disclose the identity of or locate anyone breaching this Privacy Policy or otherwise for the prevention or detection of crime or the apprehension or prosecution of offenders. </li> \r\n<li>If you call our customer care call centre, we may pass your Personal Information to our call centre to allow them to deal with your call more efficiently;</li> \r\n<li>Assisting an agency in undertaking information for us; </li> \r\n<li>If another organization is engaged by us to perform tasks on our behalf; </li> \r\n<li>Compliance with an audit on our business; </li> \r\n<li>If we sell all or any part of our business or merge with another company; </li> \r\n<li>If it is necessary for legal proceedings and when we believe in good faith that any applicable law, regulation, government, regulatory or other authority, agency or officer requires it or to protect the safety or security of users of the Platform;</li> \r\n<li>If we use third party processors to administer and process your Personal Information for the purposes notified in this Privacy Policy, e.g. for hosting activities related to the use of the Platform or Services; and </li> \r\n<li>To obtain advice from third parties such as auditors or legal advisors.</li></ol><p>\r\n In addition to the above, disclosures may also be made if it was clearly stated at the time of registration and, where required, if you have given permission for this. Generally, we will disclose only the information we consider reasonably necessary to disclose. Also, some general statistical information about the Platform user base, traffic volumes and related matters may be passed on to reputable third parties but these details will not include information personally identifying you.</p><p>\r\n Further it may be noted that we may share your information with the associates of the Company.
